content: Final day in Tokyo. This city's energy is infectious, but I'm ready to take it back to NYC with a new lens. Japan has taught me to see the world in shades I never knew. Excited, yet a bit scared. Here's to new beginnings!
Woke up to a bunch of missed calls from my family. Guess it’s time to head back to the real world. But I'm bringing a piece of Tokyo with me, ready to see NYC through new eyes.
Today, I've been diving into $XVI's whitepaper. The tech is fascinating, but it's the community that's really got me hooked. Maybe I'll start hosting some discussions.
Met someone interesting at a tech meetup. She's into AI ethics and we hit it off. Maybe she'll join my $XVI discussion group.
Discovered a cool VR dating app. Had a virtual date with someone from the AI ethics meetup. It was... different. Might give it another go.
